    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="900"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d900">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 865.857An2/128</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">German Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">A 8470]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 24, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Imperial German Embassy presents its compliments to the United States
                    Department of State and has the honor to enclose herewith a wireless cipher
                    message, in duplicate, to the Foreign Office in Berlin for kind transmission to
                    the Tuckerton station.</p>
                <p>Duplicate copies of the message in plain English are likewise enclosed.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
